HEADWORD: Oversleep
<hw>O`ver*sleep"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To sleep
beyond; <as>as, to <ex>oversleep</ex> one's self or one's usual hour of
rising</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oversleep</ent>⟦br⟧

